From Kenneth Kasajian Subject Re How can I use the mouse in NON Windows applications under MS WINDOWS Oliver Kretzschmar writes Hey, could somebody tell me, how it is possible to work with the mouse in a NON Windows application, which runs in an window We use MS WINDOWS and have CLIPPER applications Exists there any routines or something else Please mail me your informations Thanks for your efforts, Oliver NAME O Kretzschmar Inst IKE University Stuttgart PHONE Pfaffenwaldring FAX Stuttgart EMAIL Very simple You have to have the MOUSE COM or MOUSE SYS loaded in DOS before you run Windows Note that you don't need to have these files loaded to use the mouse in Windows